## tig
### easy installaiton in ubuntu

	apt-get install tig

### functions

	tig filename

will give all the commits related to the file specified
### cherry-pick

1.	do stuff on branch `dev`
2.	do `checkout master`&&`tig --all`
3.	`C` to cherry pick the commit under cursor
4.	in case of `Conflicts`, carefully follow the instruction given, and use -c <commit>.
